 # Python Project Rules Index

## Overview
These rules define the standard structure and organization for Python game projects, based on the Pyramid Math Puzzle implementation pattern.

## When to Apply
- When creating new Python projects
- When organizing existing Python projects
- When implementing game-based Python applications
- When setting up project documentation

## Rule Categories
1. Core Structure (01-03)
   - 01: Module organization and responsibilities
   - 02: Documentation graphics standards (ASCII/Mermaid)
   - 03: Mermaid diagram formatting specifications

2. Documentation (04-05)
   - 04: README structure and content requirements
   - 05: Configuration file organization

3. Project Organization (06-08)
   - 06: Directory structure and file organization
   - 07: Naming conventions for all project elements
   - 08: Dependency management and virtual environments

## Usage Guidelines
1. Start with directory structure (06)
   - Set up basic project layout
   - Create necessary directories
   - Initialize version control

2. Apply module breakdown (01)
   - Organize code into modules
   - Define module responsibilities
   - Establish module relationships

3. Follow naming conventions (07)
   - Apply consistent naming
   - Use proper case conventions
   - Follow Python standards

4. Implement documentation (02-04)
   - Create visual documentation
   - Set up README structure
   - Document module relationships

5. Set up configuration (05)
   - Organize configuration files
   - Define constants structure
   - Establish settings hierarchy

6. Manage dependencies (08)
   - Set up virtual environment
   - Create requirements files
   - Document dependencies 